    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf nvim needs to create a temporary directory but `TMPDIR` environment variable *is unset or null*, log file has a warning like the following:\n```\nWRN 2024-12-28T21:24:45.965 nvim.32125.0 vim_mktempdir:3279: $TMPDIR tempdir not a directory (or does not exist): $TMPDIR\n```\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/48c09ed4d9edd92a7c665a62aed04e8597088e60/src/nvim/os/unix_defs.h#L17\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/48c09ed4d9edd92a7c665a62aed04e8597088e60/src/nvim/fileio.c#L3275-L3282\n\n<!--I wonder why `$TMPDIR`, or `tmp` in C, is not expanded.-->\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nHere diff is used for explanation.\n\n```vim\n\" mwe.vim\nset diffexpr=MyDiff()\nfunction MyDiff()\n   silent execute \"!diff \" .. v:fname_in .. \" \" .. v:fname_new .. \" > \" .. v:fname_out\n   redraw!\nendfunction\n\n```\n\n```sh\n#!/bin/bash\nNVIM_LOG_FILE=$(mktemp)\nexport NVIM_LOG_FILE\n\nvim=nvim\ncase \"$vim\" in\n  nvim)\n    opts=(--headless);;\n  vim)\n    opts=(--log \"$NVIM_LOG_FILE\");;\nesac\n\n# when TMPDIR is not set\nunset TMPDIR\n\"$vim\" \"${opts[@]}\" -d -u mwe.vim -c qa a b\ncat \"$NVIM_LOG_FILE\"\nrm -f \"$NVIM_LOG_FILE\"\n\n# when TMPDIR is set to empty\nexport TMPDIR=\n\"$vim\" \"${opts[@]}\" -d -u mwe.vim -c qa a b\ncat \"$NVIM_LOG_FILE\"\nrm -f \"$NVIM_LOG_FILE\"\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nState that the environment variable is not set or empty (with lower level?):\n```\nWRN 2024-12-28T21:24:45.965 nvim.32125.0 vim_mktempdir:3279: $TMPDIR is unset or null\n```\n\nor expand it:\n\n```\nWRN 2024-12-28T21:24:45.965 nvim.32125.0 vim_mktempdir:3279: $TMPDIR tempdir not a directory (or does not exist): \n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-48c09ed4d9ed\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.954\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.54.2 using VTE 0.78.2 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
